════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PART 1 — PROGRAMS WRITTEN IN THE URDU PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Programs, applications, scripts, and software that you CREATE
using the Urdu Programming Language are entirely your own work.

You are free to:
  - Use, copy, modify, and distribute your programs
  - Sell your programs commercially or offer them for free
  - Release your programs as open source or keep them proprietary
  - Include your programs in other projects without restriction
  - Choose any license for your own programs

No attribution to Mohammed Zahid Wadiwale or to this project is
required for software you build using this language. Your work
is yours, with no strings attached.


════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PART 2 — THE LANGUAGE ITSELF (THIS REPOSITORY'S SOURCE CODE)
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

The source code of the Urdu Programming Language — including the
lexer, parser, transpiler, runtime, standard library modules,
documentation, and all other files in this repository — is
covered by the following terms:

1. ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENT
   Any fork, derivative work, modified version, or product based
   on this repository's source code must clearly credit:

       Original Author: Mohammed Zahid Wadiwale
       Original Project: Urdu Programming Language
       Source: https://github.com/zahid-wadiwale/urdu-lang

   This credit must appear in:
     (a) the source repository's README or equivalent documentation
     (b) any public release, package, or distribution of the
         derivative work
     (c) any user-facing "about" or "version" output, if present

2. CONTRIBUTIONS
   Contributions to this repository are welcome. By submitting a
   contribution (pull request, patch, or otherwise), you agree
   that your contribution will be included under this license.
   Contributor credit will be maintained in the project's
   contributor records (e.g., git history, CONTRIBUTORS file).
   The original authorship of Mohammed Zahid Wadiwale must remain
   acknowledged in all versions that include your contribution.

3. NO MISREPRESENTATION
   You may not claim that you created the original Urdu
   Programming Language or remove, obscure, or alter any
   attribution notices identifying Mohammed Zahid Wadiwale as the
   original author.

4. PERMITTED USES (LANGUAGE SOURCE)
   Subject to the attribution requirement above, you are permitted
   to:
     - Study, read, and learn from this source code
     - Fork and modify the language for personal or educational use
     - Create and publish a derivative language or tool, provided
       attribution is given as described above
     - Contribute improvements back to the original project

5. DISTRIBUTION OF DERIVATIVE LANGUAGES
   If you distribute a modified version of this language (source
   or binary), you must:
     (a) State clearly that your version is a modification
     (b) Retain the attribution notice in Part 2, Section 1
     (c) Not use the name "Urdu Programming Language" as the sole
         name for your fork in a way that could cause confusion
         with this original project

6. DISCLAIMER OF WARRANTY
   THIS SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY
   KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE
   WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE,
   AND NON-INFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHOR BE LIABLE
   FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES, OR OTHER LIABILITY ARISING FROM THE
   USE OF THIS SOFTWARE.


